OL,6,F"Instead, you continued driving,
OL,7,Foblivious to her, meaning that when
OL,8,FKeely stepped into the road, you
OL,9,Fcollided with her."
OL,11,FHe described Keely as a young woman
OL,12,Fwho was part of a "large family
OL,13,Fnetwork" and her loss had "devastated
OL,14,Fthose who loved her".
OL,16,FThe judge said it was "plain" that
OL,17,FWest had been driving over the 30mph
OL,18,Flimit the road had at the time.
